Text:
[II]Let us pray to Christ the Lord. He who died, and rose from the dead. He now lives and intercedes for us.
[IR]Victorious King, hear our prayer.
[I1]Christ you are the light of the world, and the salvation of nations;
[I2]set us on fire with your Spirit as we proclaim the wonder of your resurrection.
[I1]Let Israel see in you the Messiah they have longed for;
[I2]fill everyone who has breath with the knowledge of your glory.
[I1]Keep us as one, in communion, with your saints;
[I2]may we find rest with them when the work of our lives are done.
[I1]You, Jesus, have destroyed death, the final enemy of us all;
[I2]now destroy within us all that keeps us from God.
[I1]Christ, our Savior, you became obedient to death, are exalted at the right hand of the Father;
[I2]receive our siblings into the kingdom of your glory.
